column1: 125017;instagram;2018-12-04 18:39:11;FALSE;"“clutch” (life sized) from the avian show a few years ago. in her lap there is a little pile of bird skulls on a sheepskin. the skulls have been stained and gilded with metal leaf so they seem like a pile of dark jewels that she is playing with
column2: fondling and perhaps protecting. her clutch of eggs. i see her as an expression of maternal and erotic self possession. i made her before the heat of the #metoo movement was on
column3: and i have been thinking a lot about how to speak again about women and sexuality in this new cultural context. what has changed in me
column5: and all around us? i can feel my new work beginning to answer this call....

column1: 125027;instagram;2018-12-04 18:46:03;FALSE;"everyone experiences pain and wounding but trauma is something different. trauma happpens when the effects of the wound aren't allowed to process through our body. your pain is not in your mind. it's in your body.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when you wanted to run or fight or scream and you couldn't the pain got lodged in your body. that's why your body has a physical reaction when you are triggered.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column3: and body movements are so vital to the healing process. unfortunately this is something that has been frowned upon and flat out beat out of black women starting when we were children.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: 125062;instagram;2018-12-04 18:05:21;FALSE;we did it!!!! i’m officially a well-trained certified rape victim counseling advocate with the largest sexual assault advocacy in chicago called resilience! one of my many passions is advocating on the behalf of women and men who were sexually assaulted/raped. it was incredibly fun sharing this training experience with other young women who are just as passionate as i am. if it’s god will i want to go into the black communities to serve and spread the knowledge and options survivors have in order to assist in their healing process. options such as free therapy/counseling that our community didn’t think we have access too! i’m so excited!!! i know i’m a jack of all trades but this is something i share dear to my heart especially because i too am a survivor of rape and child sexual abuse. it’s a must that  i help others heal just as i did ❤️ #sexualassaultadvocate #rapevictimadvocate #survivor #metoo #love #servant #spreadknowledge #faith #instagood #instamood;;en;#SexualAssaultAdvocate

column1: 125070;instagram;2018-12-04 18:11:10;FALSE;"whilst the #metoo movement has been empowering it is far from perfect. if we really are going to make a change then we have to face up to the unintended problems the movement has created. for example it has been reported that some
men are now reluctant to have dinner with female colleagues.
some men prefer not to have one-on-one meetings with women or are no longer comfortable mentoring women.
concerns have been raised around traveling for business trips with women.
on this basis it isn’t too much of a stretch to suggest perhaps now men could be more reluctant to hire a woman?

so the question is how do we tackle these ‘reactions’ ? how do we ensure that the issue of harassment is taken seriously and tackled without having a negative impact on diversity? i would be really interested to hear your thoughts and suggestions on this...

column1: 125131;instagram;2018-12-04 16:53:10;FALSE;"want to know what we've been up in 2018? here is a list of 18 things. if you like our progress please donate today! link in bio
1) supported nine organizations/event organizers on various diversity
2) raised over $100k to fuel this important work
3) consulted with a film producer about racial representation in an upcoming documentary
4) was listed by four out of six animal charity evaluators staff members as a charity they’re excited about
5) propelled numerous people of color into prominent speaking roles as well as moderators at conferences
6) held four focus groups with professional animal advocates of color
8) supported an organization with their messaging on the mcdonald's campaign
9) supported two organizations on board recruitment
10) was interviewed for a forthcoming documentary
11) created a board with representation from various sectors of our movement
12) added three stellar advisors to our council
13) collaborated with a dei expert to build our program to support organizations
14) developed a methodology which serves as the foundation for our work with organizations
15) connected advocates of color with donors
16) supported an author on dei issues as he worked through his manuscript
17) connected with dozens of advocates of color about the unique issues they face
18) wrote about the challenges navigating funding in the #metoo era

column1: メンバーのオオカミさんは、私の横でギターを弾き、作曲をしに、そして#metoo
この楽曲は、オオカミさんが消息不明になったヴォーカル＝バンドメンバーと作りあげた作品。
そのヴォーカルさんが少しでも強くなって帰って来るまで、私が温めておこうと
、ヴォーカルレッスンで修正して今もスタジオ練習している楽曲。 －－－－－－－－－－－－－
どんなに魂込めて歌っても、このヴォーカルさんが歌うためにオオカミさんが作った2人の作品。
だからカバーにかわりはない。
それでも、ひたすら預かり温め中～🥚 作詞したヴォーカルさんが
また歌う日が来ますように
－－－－－－－－－－－－－ お陰様で、現在ライブ８本決まりました。
また、来年度は少しづつ新しい展開を見せていけたらと思っております☆

column1: 125148;instagram;2018-12-04 17:00:08;FALSE;"we thrilled to present a refreshed identity for care canada over this next year
column2: starting with our new tagline: care. bringing us together to end inequality. here' what our president and ceo
column3: gillian barth has to say about this exciting new direction:⠀

column1: we know you care enough to make a difference in the world you see and the world you experience every day. you spoke up to call for canada to do more to help syria’s refugees. you said we need to act on climate change. you were the force behind movements like #metoo. you understand that it shouldn’t be a choice between giving locally and giving internationally. we can and need to do both.⠀

care isn’t changing the way we help women and girls to lift themselves and their families out of poverty and crisis. we learned early on that putting women and girls at the centre was the best way to change things for everyone. ­­but our new tagline summarizes our renewed focus:⠀
care. bringing us together to end inequality.⠀

this statement means so much to us – and we hope it will mean more to you in the weeks and months ahead. getting people together – people who care about the same things that you and i do - has always been what we do best.⠀
we may not have invited you to big flashy events. and we’ve not been the best at simplifying the complexity of global inequality down to one or two easy issues or sentences. and the truth is
column2: that won’t change. what will change is the depth of our relationship with you.⠀

column1: for years - since our inception actually - we have been the group of passionate humanitarians that brought people (those living in poverty
column5: to learn and to start a ripple of change that continues on to this day.""⠀

column1: 125180;instagram;2018-12-04 16:26:47;FALSE;"workplace sexual harassment is an emergency and no employer can afford to delay in addressing it. that’s because not only do its victims face lifelong physical and psychological issues
column2: sexual harassment can also destroy an organisation’s brand

column1: the sexual harassment of women at workplace (prevention
column3: 2013 makes it compulsory for every employer with 10 or employees to set up an internal complaints committee (icc) to redress sexual harassment complaints by their female workforce. the law also makes it mandatory for the icc to complete its inquiry within 90 days of receiving a complaint and take action within 60 days of the inquiry concluding. .

column1: 125354;instagram;2018-12-04 13:05:39;FALSE;"#敏感一點也沒關係 ：給女生看的共鳴小品
韓國近年有很多小清新網劇，每集才10分鐘的網劇非常易入口，女主角是《當你沉睡時》裡的咖啡店員工（那時看的時候就覺得她挺漂亮的），剪短了頭髮更可愛了。男主角好像演過幾套網劇的主角，雖然長相不是典型靚仔，但身型高大，劇中的性格完全是理想男友。
看第一集還以為是校園青春春劇，但看著看著才發現是給女生看的窩心小品。大概每個女生都會有共鳴吧，生活中有被看輕、被欺負、被騷擾的感覺，但總會反問：「是自己太敏感了嗎？」而忍氣吞聲、小事化無。這些無奈和不忿的感覺，相信很多人都有經歷過。
劇集最後點題 #metoo 和 #withyou ，近年 #metoo 其實真的有點變質也令人有負面感覺，但想深一層難道就因此要成為沉默的受害者？
如果能堅強一點，告訴自己和身邊的人，敏感一點也沒關係，才是真正的平權。
p.s. 除了劇情有意思外，男女主角的互動也很甜蜜很好看。

column1: the thing with revisiting such a classic piece of cinema after seeing more contemporary works is you can't help but notice well-trodden themes along the way
column2: making it feel somewhat less distinctive–which is ironic as it is the original. rosemary's baby follows the titular character (splendidly played by mia farrow) who grows increasingly suspicious that her husband (john cassavetes) and nosy elderly neighbors (sidney blackmer and ruth gordon) are plotting a conspiracy against her and her baby. it's such a seminal work that
column4: its influence is still clearly felt.

column1: polanski's hollywood debut gave birth to notable elements utilized by modern horror
column2: with movies like the omen (1976) and the exorcist (1973) soon followed suit with a satanic-centric narrative. rosemary's baby's influence in the last couple of years alone remains strongly apparent
column3: with stunning works like hereditary (2018) and indo's own pengabdi setan (2017) taking their own spin on satanic cults and evil offsprings. jordan peel's get out (2017) also took on the evil cult narrative
column4: honing in on the paranoia and panic involved in being gaslighted by those close to you. even without the satanic elements
column5: get out actually shares a closer thematic kinship with the movie than the other two; get out is as much about the black experience as rosemary's baby is about being a woman in such a dismissive society.

column1: rosemary is this doting and dutiful wife who is controlled by the men around her; her opinions and choices get shot down directly
column2: as she is treated as a mere object to advance the lives of said men. this feels especially relevant in the #metoo era
column3: even more so with polanski's own string of sexual abuse cases. like with woody allen and kevin spacey
column4: it's one of those cases where the artist themself taints the perception of their art; it's more than disappointing to know that such a visionary piece came from such a problematic individual.

column2: rosemary's baby remains a fascinating and timeless cinematic work
column3: as its few dated dialogues and director's infamy are outweighed by its legacy.

column1: 125437;instagram;2018-12-04 11:36:05;FALSE;"jedes lernen hat einen äußeren und einen inneren prozess bei mir. alles muss erst sacken um dann erneut
der kurs am wochenende mit @kathrin_branderuptannous bei kati @equinality hat viel bewegt und verdeutlicht.
besonders die bewegte theorie zu beginn hat mir gezeigt: meine grenzen muss ich klarer benennen und nach mehrfacher übertretung durch andere
column2: ist eine pause angebrachter als ein erneuter versuch!

column1: somit lernte ich bewusst durch/für/ von mir/mich und auch durch/von anderen. die praxiseinheiten waren so angenehm zu beobachten. jeder teilnehmer wurde empathisch begleitet und angeleitet. wissen wurde auf augenhöhe vermittelt und so ausgekleidet
column2: dass der jeweilige schüler es gut aufnehmen
column3: umsetzen und festigen konnte. ich sensitives „weichei“ war so angetan von dem umgang und dem toll formulierten wissen
column4: dass ich kati direkt mitteilte 2019 dabei sein zu wollen mit otis. so wertschätzend
column5: respektvoll und voller toller bilder bin ich noch nicht ganz so oft von einem seminar gekommen. mein kopf sang die ganzen 2 std rückfahrt: wie wilde

column1: zudem spielte ich viel mit dem bild der sitz-füße 🦶🏽 und bin ganz begeistert
column2: denn es bringt mein gefühl beim reiten in ein so logisches und faszinierendes bild voller facetten.

column3: danke an alle die dieses wochenende zu dem gemacht haben

column1: 125443;instagram;2018-12-04 11:39:55;FALSE;i saw aly raisman speak last night.  she is a really impressive woman.  i was so pleased to hear her speak so highly about the importance of her daily meditation practice.  she has become an activist for body positivity and the #metoo movement.  meditation keeps her centered amidst talking about her dark days of suffering from sexual abuse and being body shamed for her muscles.  thank you
column3: for the fantastic work you do. thank you for teaching the crowd (many of whom were young girls) about meditation and using it for intuitive eating.  thank you for teaching them how to identify kind people to spend your time with and not people who make you feel bad. thank you for talking about your partnership with darkness to light— i will do the training as a kids yoga teacher to identify children who may be suffering from abuse. metta

column1: 1972년작 '파리에서의 마지막 탱고'는 단연 베르나도 베르톨루치의 대표작으로 꼽힌다. 개봉 당시 이 작품은 과감한 성적 표현 때문에 논란을 일으켰고
column2: 이탈리아에서는 20년 가까이 상영이 금지되기도 했다. 그에게 세계적인 명성을 안겨다 준 이 작품은 최근 말론 브란도와 여배우 마리아 슈나이더(당시 19세)의 섹스신이 '성폭행'이었다는 의혹이 제기되면서 논란이 불거지기도 했다.

column1: 촬영 당시의 성폭행에 관련한 숨은 이야기는 아이러니하게도 베르톨루치 감독 자신이 지난 2013년 인터뷰를 통해 언급하면서 세상에 알려지기 시작했다. 영화의 초반부
column2: 우연히 만난 두 남녀가 파리의 어느 한 아파트에서 섹스를 하는 이 문제의 장면에 관해
column3: 베르톨루치는 여주인공 슈나이더의 동의를 받지 않고 강간 장면을 촬영했다고 스스로 털어놓았다. 그는 브란도와 함께 이 장면을 계획했다는 사실도 덧붙였다.

column2: 실제 강간의 리액션을 촬영함으로 연기가 아닌 분노와 수치심을 카메라에 담고자 했다고 고백했고 죄책감을 느끼지만 후회하지는 않는다고 말했다.

column1: 그러나 작품의 완성도를 위한 작가의 열의라는 차원에서 이해해줄 수 있는 사항은 아니다. 2011년 사망한 슈나이더는 생존시 촬영 당시의 강간당한 느낌을 기회 있을 때마다 토로했었다. 세상 물정을 모르는 19세의 젊은 여성을 '기만'했다는 이유 하나 만으로도 베르톨루치 감독은 비난의 대상이 되기에 충분하다.

column2: 시나리오에 없는 합의되지 않은 섹스는 오늘 날의 법개념으로 해석하면 '강간'에 해당한다. 이 사실이 알려지자 베르톨루치 감독과 말론 브란도는 많은 영화팬들에게 증오의 대상으로 떠올랐다.

column1: 김정 | 영화평론가 | korea daily news | 미주중앙일보 | 12.1.2018 🎬
1972년작 '파리에서의 마지막 탱고'는 단연 베르나도 베르톨루치의 대표작으로 꼽힌다. 개봉 당시 이 작품은 과감한 성적 표현 때문에 논란을 일으켰고
column2: 이탈리아에서는 20년 가까이 상영이 금지되기도 했다. 그에게 세계적인 명성을 안겨다 준 이 작품은 최근 말론 브란도와 여배우 마리아 슈나이더(당시 19세)의 섹스신이 '성폭행'이었다는 의혹이 제기되면서 논란이 불거지기도 했다.

column1: 촬영 당시의 성폭행에 관련한 숨은 이야기는 아이러니하게도 베르톨루치 감독 자신이 지난 2013년 인터뷰를 통해 언급하면서 세상에 알려지기 시작했다. 영화의 초반부
column2: 우연히 만난 두 남녀가 파리의 어느 한 아파트에서 섹스를 하는 이 문제의 장면에 관해
column3: 베르톨루치는 여주인공 슈나이더의 동의를 받지 않고 강간 장면을 촬영했다고 스스로 털어놓았다. 그는 브란도와 함께 이 장면을 계획했다는 사실도 덧붙였다.

column2: 실제 강간의 리액션을 촬영함으로 연기가 아닌 분노와 수치심을 카메라에 담고자 했다고 고백했고 죄책감을 느끼지만 후회하지는 않는다고 말했다.

column1: 그러나 작품의 완성도를 위한 작가의 열의라는 차원에서 이해해줄 수 있는 사항은 아니다. 2011년 사망한 슈나이더는 생존시 촬영 당시의 강간당한 느낌을 기회 있을 때마다 토로했었다. 세상 물정을 모르는 19세의 젊은 여성을 '기만'했다는 이유 하나 만으로도 베르톨루치 감독은 비난의 대상이 되기에 충분하다.

column2: 시나리오에 없는 합의되지 않은 섹스는 오늘 날의 법개념으로 해석하면 '강간'에 해당한다. 이 사실이 알려지자 베르톨루치 감독과 말론 브란도는 많은 영화팬들에게 증오의 대상으로 떠올랐다.

idag var första gången jag var på samtal på frideborg utan att prata om min exman. denna gången pratade jag bara om andra män
column2: framförallt män på min senaste arbetsplats. jag har haft en säsongsanställning tre år i rad hos en stor lokal hyresvärd. 2016
column3: min första sommar (bara ett halvår efter separation från nex och ca två-tre månader efter senaste självmordsförsöket) började jag inbilla mig att en av mina chefer flirtade med mig....jag var inte fysiskt attraherad av honom men jag mådde bra i hans sällskap
column4: han hyllade mig och sträckte min tro på mig själv. det var intellektuellt stimulerande att vara i hans närhet och han hjälpte även mig att fixa en lägenhet. vi hade en messengerkontakt som till en början var hur oskyldig som helst men sakta blev värre o värre. vi träffades så en dag efter jobbet o åt o gick en promenad. en promenad som slutade med att han sa ”jag hoppas du är rakad” samtidigt som han tryckte ner sin hand i mina byxor och stoppade upp ett finger i mig för att sedan suga av fingret samtidigt som han intensivt stirrade mig rakt i ögonen. jag stod som förlamad och sa ingenting. hela vägen hem frågade jag mig själv vad fan hände och varför jag inte bara gav honom en fet smäll???

column1: jag bröt all privat kontakt efter det och fick snyftningar om att han gick över gränsen och önskade att jag ville ge honom en chans att visa att han var en bra man bla bla bla. jag berättade självklart för vänner om det som hänt men inte någon annan högre i företaget. jag ursäktade hans uppträdande för mig själv med att han (trots att han hade sambo) typ förälskat sig i mig o det hela spårade ur. denna sommar (2018) har han varit på en annan kvinna på jobbet (trots att hans sambo var höggravid)
column2: smickrar henne och bjöd ut henne på en lunch som slutade med att han tagit hennes hand och tryckt den mot sitt kön....men han är högt respekterad och dessutom en bra referens så hon vill inte att jag berättar för någon....frustrationen kryper i mig och när jag fick veta att han varit på henne fick jag en helt annan syn på det som hänt mig. det var absolut inte ok och jag kände mig fruktansvärt äcklad. #metoo #sexuelltofredande";;en;#metoo

column1: 125468;instagram;2018-12-04 10:45:53;FALSE;i want to tell you how my date went on friday... as soon as i saw jamie with flowers and limo i felt like a princess... but as we came to the grand hotel restaurant i felt judgmental stares on me and was so embarrassed how i dressed. how was i supposed to know it was so formal there? then jamie started asking me some scientific questions.. i didnt understand a thing he said! i felt like a fool... so i decided to change the subject and get some sugar. as i reached i spilled my coffee all over white tablecloth... i tried to rub it off but it just made it worse. i scoffed all the cake and drank all champagne quickly( since is was all so expensive)  to leave this place. i thought jamie would never want to see me again after i made such a mess... but instead he asked me where i'd like to go next. so we grabbed some maccas chippies and i took him to a nearby park. we laughed

column1: 125482;instagram;2018-12-04 10:55:34;FALSE;"@thejimmydoreshow @foxnews @cnn i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.
steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?
abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me
column2: a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

column1: the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.
and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

;tw tekstissä ja videossa : seksuaalinen väkivalta , seksuaalinen trauma , jähmettymisreaktio , fyysinen liikkumattomuus , seksuaalisten tekojen suostumuksellisuus . juttu löytyy : . . . anne kantola kirjoittaa helsingin sanomissa , nyt- kolumnissaan : ulkopuolelta helppo sanoa , miten ihmisten tulisi toimia vaaratilanteissa : pakene , huuda apua , suojaa itsesi . samat neuvot toistuvat myös seksuaalisiin ahdisteluihin ja väärinkäytöksiin liittyessä . huuda apua , taistele vastaan , pakene . meistä jokainen ei kuitenkaan pysty taistelemaan . osa ei pysty sanomaan edes ” ei ” . ei silloinkaan kun epätoivottu ihminen rupeaa repimään vaatteita päältämme . miksi näin ? meistä kukaan ei voi ennalta tietää , miten toimii niissä tilanteissa , joissa omia rajoja yllättäen aletaan rikkoa . ” emme aina toimi niin kuin elokuvissa , emmekä pysty taistelemaan . aivomme pyrkii siihen , että ihminen säilyy hengissä ” , sanoo väestöliiton erityisasiantuntija kirsi porras . jos aivomme tulkitsevat uhkaavan tilanteen niin , että fyysisesti olemme jäämässä alakynteen , hermostomme reaktiona voi vastaan taistelun sijaan olla kehon lamaantuminen . jäädymme siis täysin . avaamme suun huutaaksemme , mutta ääntä ei tule . jähmetymme aloillemme , ja toivomme että kaikki olisi ohi mahdollisimman nopeasti . jähmettyminen ei tietenkään tarkoita sitä , että tilanne olisi ok. se sellaista hiljaisuutta , joka ei ole myöntymisen merkki . se tapa suojella itseämme ja puolustautua passiivisuudella . seksuaalinen trauma erityinen , koska trauman aiheuttaa toinen ihminen tahallisesti tilanteessa , joka muuten liittyy hyvän tekemiseen toiselle ihmiselle . seksuaalisesta traumasta voi toipua , mutta se vaatii usein keskusteluapua . keskustelutukea löydät www.netari.fi , www.vaestoliitto.fi/nuoret , www.nuoenexit.fi , www.nuoret.riku.fi , loistosetlementti.fi . lausunto seksuaalisen trauman vaikutuksesta nuoreen oikeudenkäyntilausunto > www.vaestoliitto.fi/ > ;prendo prestito le parole di per diffondere , ritardo , un messaggio impoante : '' < dovete guardare come era vestita : indossava un perizoma di pizzo nero . questo non indica forse che la ragazza era attratta dall'uomo che si aspettava di avere un incontro ? > è con questa argomentazione difensiva che un ventisettenne di cork , la scorsa settimana , è stato assolto un processo cui era accusato di aver stuprato una diciassettenne . perché secondo il suo avvocato difensore ( donna , peraltro ) c'è un legame automatico fra la biancheria che una persona indossa e la sua disponibilità sessuale . perché secondo lei , se una donna decide di mettersi addosso qualcosa di provocan note ha sempre il secondo fine di sedurre , non può farlo per sé . la ragazza poteva non aspettarsi alcun incontro . poteva invece aspettarselo , salvo poi cambiare idea . può persino essersi inventata l'accusa di violenza ( anche se le sono state trovate le tracce sul suo corpo ) . indipendentemente da tutto questo , il tribunale ha considerato valida questa argomentazione , che la reputa ( almeno pae ) responsabile della violenza subita per via del suo compoamento . ed è inaccettabile . lo è prescindere , figuriamoci con la nuova consapevolezza che il mondo sta guadagdo riguardo la questione delle molestie . è il momento -anzi è già molto tardi- cui dire chiaramente basta . basta farsi andare bene un sistema che continua dare la colpa di una violenza tutto tranne chi davvero ( e soltanto ) la ha , cioè l'ha commessa . basta . '' grazie ancora per il magnifico post ( lo trovate sul suo profilo ) . mi sento solo di aggiungere che non è neanche consenso il fatto di `` essere uomini '' . non è vero che se il tuo paner è uomo allora vorrà sicuramente fare sesso . anche loro hanno il diritto del consenso . lo stupro maschile esiste . ;[('prendo'

column1: 125550;instagram;2018-12-04 08:56:13;FALSE;"""i was on my way home from a tuition class in the evening
column2: and the bus was very crowded. there was a man seated next to me
column3: i didn't notice him at first
column5: i realised his hand was on my inner thigh.  i was so shocked and it took me a few seconds to realise what was happening. that was the first time i was harassed physically and i didn't know how to react. i got so angry. i asked him directly
column6: 'what's your problem? what are you doing?' he said
column9: i hit him with my water bottle. i couldn't believe that the bus conductor
column10: driver and other passengers didn't help me. a lady seated next to him saw what happened but she didn't say anything. i know that violence is not the answer but in that moment that was my instant reaction. after some time
column11: i told my parents about it. my father said that man may not try that with another girl after this incident"" - shiyalini

column1: 京都でも有名な寺町、新京極を三条に抜けて少し西に向かい昔の銀行のような建物が目印。
脇に見落としそうな入り口が…
話には聞いていたので凄く緊張しながら入店、、、しようと思ったけど入り口が分からずウロウロ  笑
ようやく見つけた入り口から入るとしばらく通路を歩いた先には静かな""the bar""の雰囲気。
シガーも吸いたかった自分は更に奥のホールへ
するとそこは映画等でマフィアがやり取りをしてるワンシーンを切り取った様な、静かで少し暗く落ち着いた空間。
分からない事だらけやったけど、全部丁寧に教えてもらってシガーの楽しみ方を教えてもらいました( ´∀｀)
大好きなウイスキーもあったので、それも2杯ほど頂き大満足🍸
やはり雰囲気云々もあって値段もいい値段しましたけど、それ以上に楽しめたので寧ろ安く感じました。

column1: 125683;instagram;2018-12-04 06:55:06;FALSE;"the colours aren't beautiful for a victim of rape.
i was 9 when i was bribed with food
column2: toya and money in exchange for something ""fun"". as a child
column3: i didn't know that ""fun"" thing we did was wrong.

column1: it was later that i knew that i was ""raped"". i've been silent about it for a long time. i know people will cease to believe me
column2: to empathize with me. ""no guy ever gets harassed
column3: no guy ever gets raped"". a similar trauma happened when i was in college. it was an open house party
column4: i was drinking. little do i know that i am an easy target for people with bad intentions. i fell asleep
column5: i fell for the trap. my body was heavy
column7: out. i had marks all over me
column8: marks that weren't there before. i was sore.

column1: i kept quiet. and pointed all fingers at me. it was fault! i blame myself. the silence of what had happened became a heavy baggage for me to carry. and i thought the silence would help me forget. i thought wrong. sometimes i still do blame myself
column2: but is it really my fault?

125708;instagram;2018-12-04 05:44:50;FALSE;are you aware of the privilege you have to make the choices in life that you do? this is something i am in constant conversation with myself about. i am white
column2: middle class. with that comes a degree of privilege. and

column1: i have worked hard - hard - harder - to be where i am today
column2: and i am not riding free. i am also a single mother. that means
column3: certain choices are not available to me. i lament that my kids are not involved in as many after-school activities as many of my peers and remind myself that they are thriving nonetheless.

column1: i am a single mother of one of my children who lives with me full time. that means
column3: mostly the choices that have to do with embracing ""single"" and cultivating friendships and a dating life that mothers whose counterparts take partial custody get to choose where i have to not be away too much.

column1: i am a single mother of two children who experienced trauma due to the dysfunction of the marriage i was in
column2: and the subsequent strains of the divorce. that means
column4: mostly the choices that my children would make to be in the world
column5: are not as ""safe"" or available to them as to many of their peers.

column1: i say this not to ask for pity or attention. in fact
column2: i never post publicly when that is my motive. i say this because privilege is real
column3: and it is relative. it is
column5: something you do not appreciate until it is taken from you. and
column7: until you develop a deep understanding for the experience of others
column8: you will not see or recognize the impacts of your own privilege.

column1: agency = seeing the choices that are available to you
not everyone can see the choices that are available to them.
”all are welcome” does not equal ""all feel welcome."" #privilege #metoo #socialjustice #yoga #yogamama #yogamom #singlemom #yogatherapy #yogatherapist #phoenixrisingyogatherapy";;en;#privilege

column3: i did not know where to go. i felt alone
column8: unsafe etc. i was looking for a lighthouse of sanctuary to feel safe and understand more deeply what i was experiencing. sometimes i wonder if it wasn’t for my baby and the peak of abuse that the pregnancy triggered that brought my clarity that i was actually being abused and not just dating a toxic person
column9: would i still be in the pattern?

column6: some people don’t want to acknowledge that my former partner is an abuser. it’s easier to believe charm and facade than to believe the potential darker side of the coin. i’ve heard “that’s interesting karma” and “everything happens for a reason”. and sure whatever

column9: “you’ve been abused and yet you don’t treat people that way. that’s how you know it’s a choice. a choice he makes again and again”. abusers aren’t stupid
column11: they’re smart enough to be covert and they’re smart enough to keep the “game” in their favor as long as you don’t understand the rules.

column1: 125738;instagram;2018-12-04 04:40:02;FALSE;"@arimelber ❤ @maddowshow 💪😘👍 i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.
steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?
abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me
column2: a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

column1: the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

a belief as to a weighty and substantial aspect of human life and behaviour
attain a certain level of cogency
be worthy of respect in a democratic society

column1: 125808;instagram;2018-12-04 03:01:08;FALSE;"moon in scorpio. the deepest part of the water we fear to know we share. (<read that again) this moon went into the house of the scorpion around 1pm today. last night it danced with uranus
column2: the planet of revolution; today it met with venus
column3: the planet of what we really value & call precious. idk tho- today was on fast forward for me. all day was weird
column4: surreal & impossible. the spirits were breaking things & mercury rx was in hyper drive. i suspect i was meant to notice important things (because i am always chiming in that you should) but i didn’t notice anything but how impossible it was to be at all today. i just sloshed around like a newbie at life. i had a weird head/eye ache. i know i’ll see it in my chart once i can focus my eyes again. whew! how are you babes!? what was your day like? i think we’re in for some interesting downloads with this moon in scorpio. i found my self planning to watch a sad move so i could have a good cry. my capricorn moon sometimes needs that motivation. i guess i could also just watch the damn news. i don’t know babes. scorpio is the sign where we’ve had some very harsh & startling growth over the last year. maybe the universe was just deflecting so we didn’t have to take it all in at once? all we’ve seen
column8: felt in the last year: it’s been a lot. we started a healing process but it’s far from over. i’m calling it the “physical therapy” part of the #metoo movement. we bandaged
column9: stitched & scabbed over but now we must start learning to move around again. we must learn to engage & interact in this new skin. we know there is still so much to fix too. validate the hardness of this time. try to give your self & others some room to slosh around too. just see if you can take it easy in the deep waters of scorpio. float. breathe. notice. just be. goodness it is a challenge in these weathers but it feels like resistance won’t werk well rn. maybe i’m wrong but i don’t think i have the energy to ponder it much more after today. let’s see how tomorrow feels when the moon approaches mercury rx- perhaps that trickers has some answers for us as he slows down to stop this rx nonsense this week. either way

column2: we are aware of our experiences with sexual violence & collective suffering. we have shared these stories many times over and still carry the trauma in our bones. my hope is for our women's wisdom to become a resource for real revolution
column3: instead of adding to the archives of our aggregate agony.

column1: i'd like to take this opportunity to talk about some experiences wwith sexual harassment

column2: i wore a sports jacket every day. i would seldom take off this protective layer
column3: because it was my first survival tactic for preventing sexual harassment from peers and older men
column4: at school & in the streets. in retrospect
column5: i wonder what could have been if as young girls we were to come together
column7: and act in solidarity by disrupting & dismantling sexual harassment together at an early age.

column2: i caught glimpses of what this could look like. i have had women save me from men following me on the street. once
column3: i was being followed at night & literally prayed my way into fast food place. i was offered sanctuary by an latina migrant worker
column4: despite the dine-in area being closed. another instance
column5: i was waiting at a bus stop. a man pulled up & tried to solicit sex. when the light turned green
column6: a woman rolled up in her suv & shouted
column7: ""are you ok? is this man bothering you!? do you need a ride?"" & the man drove off immediately! both these instances
column9: have demonstrated the effectiveness of sisterhood & taking direct action against sexual harassment. but what about a more collective strategy for feminist movement & achieving women's liberation?

column1: we have seen the power of women's organized fury with the explosion of the #metoo movement & repercussions for perpetrators as a result. we have also discussed it's discontents & the decentering of woc struggles. so
column3: transnational feminist future look like? what elements of it already exist here & now? we believe that transnational woc have not only the capacity

column1: i'd like to take this opportunity to talk about some experiences wwith sexual harassment

column2: i wore a sports jacket every day. i would seldom take off this protective layer
column3: because it was my first survival tactic for preventing sexual harassment from peers and older men
column4: at school & in the streets. in retrospect
column5: i wonder what could have been if as young girls we were to come together
column7: and act in solidarity by disrupting & dismantling sexual harassment together at an early age.

column2: i caught glimpses of what this could look like. i have had women save me from men following me on the street. once
column3: i was being followed at night & literally prayed my way into fast food place. i was offered sanctuary by an latina migrant worker
column4: despite the dine-in area being closed. another instance

column6: a woman rolled up in her suv & shouted
column7: ""are you ok? is this man bothering you!? do you need a ride?"" & the man drove off immediately! both these instances
column9: have demonstrated the effectiveness of sisterhood & taking direct action against sexual harassment. but what about a more collective strategy for feminist movement & achieving women's liberation?

column1: 125816;instagram;2018-12-04 03:06:02;FALSE;"it will always strike me as incredible how one moment that lasted a few minutes can change one’s life. ⠀⠀
i don’t want to sleep at night because i see your face in my nightmares.
i wake up in the morning with you on my mind.
i can’t stand to be in crowded places because i’m afraid that something will happen to me.
i feel it happening over and over again.
i couldn’t sleep under the covers for a month because it reminded me of that night.
i can’t wear certain pants because they remind me of that night.
i freak out when i hear a fan blowing because you had your fan on high that night.
i chopped my own hair off because it reminded me of the choking sensation i experienced that night as my long hair wrapped around my neck

column1: i can’t promise it will get better but i can promise i will walk this journey with you. i think we should take a moment and just cry. it’s okay. it’s okay to not be happy and it’s okay for people to state that you seem happy. we can do this. we can make it through this. from one day to the next your thoughts
column3: emotions and reactions can and will change. you know this better than anyone. its okay to let people in and tell them how you are feeling. there are so many people who say all the wrong things because they don’t know what to say. so when we tell them we need them. we can also say “i need you to come and sit with me and bring wine and then just let me talk. the more we talk this out of our systems the more we can actually make choices for ourselves. we can actually chose to be happy. the more we talk about it the more control we have over it. when it stays in our heads and hearts and has no outlet it grows into a monster and keeps us in its control.  we are no longer victims. we are survivors. #awomanscorned #letstalk #sexualabuse #sexualabuseawareness #metoo #melodiethurman #chosehappiness";;en;#awomanscorned

125879;instagram;2018-12-03 08:42:53;FALSE;model初體驗，自己發自己通告的概念。
這是一家男裝牌子在舉辦試穿活動，我看到可以穿三件就很開心地報名，也沒想到其實我本人沒什麼benefit🤣
拍攝交由技術越來越好的同事沒力，在要交一堆報表的禮拜一被我硬逼著當攝影師😅
拍攝過程整個只記得小時候家政老師說的表現優點隱藏缺點，但她好像沒有說全身都是缺點的時候要怎麼處理。
至於褲子好不好穿，老實說我覺得料子很讚，但畢竟一件也是$2

column1: 125891;instagram;2018-12-04 01:13:23;FALSE;"i feel like i haven’t properly introduced myself so let’s do it!! my names  carmen i’m 16 years old and i created this page to kind of be a safe space for not only myself but to others as well. over the course of my life i’ve dealt  with many traumas that have molded me into the person i am today
column2: i deal with a loved one who is an addict
column3: i am a survivor (never victim) of sexual assault and now i am also learning to cope with the recent passing of m my father. now i know that those things seem very dark— which they are and yes if your wondering those things have taken a toll on my mental health as well as my physical health i’ve been dealing with anxiety for as long as i can remember but what with the grace of gods calling i decided to create this page to shed lots of light on my situation and also hear others who feel they aren’t heard. i believe there is always good in any situation or at least good you can make of it. therefore this page will be apart of my testimony of strength to overcome darkness and dwelling. i love topics that deal with women’s rights
column7: as well as the rights of minorities and blacks. like i said this page is to shed light on things that are left in the dark and for you yes you to feel that you are the best you can be despite your trials and tribulations that you are okay here and your voice and story matters and that you and your mental health(your overall health periodt) come first 💛 ~follow @yalocalselfcaresis ~

column1: 難過的時候，就讓受傷的情緒哭出來吧
let your tears take away those bad feeling
tommorrow is always a new day
台灣2018年底的大選綁公投
也許讓很多人受傷難過，不如預期
但請記得大法官釋憲對同志婚姻的肯定
請記得不論世界怎麼變化
你是一個人來到這世界，
你是很重要的，獨一無二的個體，
outcome of taiwan's referendum and election in november 2018 may hurt lots people's feeling
but please remember the constitutional interpretation already light up the light ahead
and remember that despite the world doesn't seem to be friendly and justice sometimes
you are a very very unique and important individual
you have to find your mission in this world
我在生命最低谷的幾年
哭了就是憂鬱，快喪失對世界的任何熱情
後來是在友善團體與資源的陪伴下
just cry and healing will comes after that
i cry and in serious depression
column2: kind of lose any interest and hope to the world

column1: 京都の繁華街にあるオーセンティックbar c&d
先斗町と木屋町にあり
先斗町はジン、木屋町はウイスキーが数多く置いてある
今回は僕がウイスキー好きということもあり木屋町店にお邪魔してきました
ビルの中にあるせいでちょっと入り口がわかりにくい、、、
でも、入ってみたら落ち着いた大人の空間やぁ( ´∀｀)
カウンター越しに見る沢山のウイスキーはまさに圧巻。barにきたなぁって感じがする
ウイスキーとカクテルを一杯ずつ作ってもらったけどやっぱりバーテンダーがお酒作ってる作業ってかっこいい。
見た目イカつかったけど  笑
女の子と二人でデートとかで使ったらウケも良さそう
今回は2杯だけやったこともあって金額も全然いってなかったしまた休みの日にでもふらっと行こうかな
